234
00:16:42,980 --> 00:16:44,220
I really have!

235
00:16:44,220 --> 00:16:50,490
I even memorized Dr. Alexandria's Seventh Principle, and you told me it was the hardest one.

236
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:53,990
"Tabo-tabo bacteria start to degrade on the seventh day of the culture microbe..."

237
00:16:53,990 --> 00:16:57,790
...as detailed in section 2, chapter 7, page 1254...

238
00:16:57,790 --> 00:17:00,300
"...after the sign of overreaction appears..."

239
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:03,680
Hmph. So... what...?

240
00:17:08,670 --> 00:17:09,930
Doctorine!

241
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:13,040
Are you alright!?

242
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:17,770
It seems I've caught something from that patient I saw the other day.

243
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:19,400
You have a terrible fever!

244
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:23,590
Chopper, you've been making all these grand statements about your medical skills,

245
00:17:23,590 --> 00:17:25,240
so show something for it.

246
00:17:27,330 --> 00:17:30,270
I'll be your first parient.

247
00:17:31,970 --> 00:17:35,460
I won't give you even one piece of advice.

248
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:38,860
If you fail, I will die.

249
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:41,680
Learn through experience.

250
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:46,640
Learn that medical science is a deadly fight with a patient's life.

251
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:50,660
Can a blue-nosed reindeer win that fight?

252
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:14,080
I'm sure now!

253
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:16,350
This is Mondrin bacillus!

254
00:18:16,350 --> 00:18:17,940
The medicine which kills this bacillus...

255
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:20,600
This is it.

256
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:26,500
Doctorine...

257
00:18:27,970 --> 00:18:29,160
Don't die...

258
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:29,970
Please!

259
00:18:38,210 --> 00:18:39,230
Let me see.

260
00:18:41,670 --> 00:18:45,450
Aren't you going to ask what's in it?

261
00:18:45,450 --> 00:18:49,680
There is no patient who has room in their heart to ask such a queation.

262
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:54,250
Illnesses can't be cured unless a patient completely trusts their doctor.

263
00:18:58,270 --> 00:18:59,560
How is it?

264
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:00,890
Do you fell better?

265
00:19:00,890 --> 00:19:01,710
Idiot.

266
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:04,320
No medicine starts working that fast.

267
00:19:04,320 --> 00:19:06,530
Let me sleep for a little while.

268
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:26,970
Chopper!

269
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:31,020
It was very good work, for someone like you.

270
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:38,660
